District heating networks supply heat to residential and commercial customers. The utility operates several heat production plants and thermal storage units. Heat can be produced from different fuel types, stored temporarily, and distributed through a network that incurs losses. The objective is to maximize profit from heat sales while respecting operational limits and environmental regulations.

